––– comment –––
Test for issue #3428: total_found with HAVING clause
https://github.com/manticoresoftware/manticoresearch/issues/3428

Issue: total_found was returning count of all groups, not filtered groups after HAVING.
This broke pagination as total_found didn't reflect actual result count.

Test validates:
1. HAVING filters groups correctly (total_found < all groups)
2. total_found stable across paginated queries
3. Edge cases (empty results, stricter filters)
––– block: ../base/start-searchd-with-buddy –––
––– comment –––
Create table with 10K rows across ~200 categories (uneven distribution for HAVING testing)
––– input –––
manticore-load --quiet --json --init="CREATE TABLE test_having (id bigint, category int, price float, quantity int)" --load="INSERT INTO test_having (id, category, price, quantity) VALUES (<increment>, <int/1/200>, <float/10.0/100.0>, <int/1/50>)" --batch-size=1000 --threads=4 --total=10000 > /dev/null; echo $?
––– output –––
0
––– comment –––
Verify: 10K rows loaded
––– input –––
mysql -h0 -P9306 -e "SELECT COUNT(*) FROM test_having;"
––– output –––
+----------+
| count(*) |
+----------+
|    10000 |
+----------+
––– comment –––
Verify: ~200 distinct categories exist
––– input –––
mysql -h0 -P9306 -e "SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT category) as distinct_categories FROM test_having;"
––– output –––
+---------------------+
| distinct_categories |
+---------------------+
|                 200 |
+---------------------+
––– comment –––
TEST 1: Get total_found with HAVING filter (cnt > 30)
––– input –––
TOTAL_WITH_HAVING=$(mysql -h0 -P9306 -e "SELECT category, COUNT(*) as cnt FROM test_having GROUP BY category HAVING cnt > 30 LIMIT 1; SHOW META LIKE 'total_found';" | grep total_found | grep -oE '[0-9]+'); echo "Groups with cnt > 30: $TOTAL_WITH_HAVING"
––– output –––
Groups with cnt > 30: 199
––– comment –––
TEST 2: Get total_found without HAVING (baseline - all groups)
––– input –––
TOTAL_WITHOUT_HAVING=$(mysql -h0 -P9306 -e "SELECT category, COUNT(*) as cnt FROM test_having GROUP BY category LIMIT 1; SHOW META LIKE 'total_found';" | grep total_found | grep -oE '[0-9]+'); echo "All groups: $TOTAL_WITHOUT_HAVING"
––– output –––
All groups: 200
––– comment –––
CRITICAL: Verify HAVING filters groups (with HAVING < without HAVING)
Old bug: both values equal, new: with HAVING should be less
––– input –––
if [ "$TOTAL_WITH_HAVING" -lt "$TOTAL_WITHOUT_HAVING" ]; then echo "SUCCESS: HAVING filtered groups correctly - All groups: $TOTAL_WITHOUT_HAVING, Filtered: $TOTAL_WITH_HAVING"; else echo "FAIL: BUG DETECTED - total_found ignores HAVING filter (Both show: $TOTAL_WITHOUT_HAVING groups)"; fi
––– output –––
SUCCESS: HAVING filtered groups correctly - All groups: 200, Filtered: 199
––– comment –––
TEST 3: Pagination page 1 (OFFSET 0) - check total_found
––– input –––
TOTAL_FOUND_PAGE1=$(mysql -h0 -P9306 -e "SELECT category, COUNT(*) as cnt FROM test_having GROUP BY category HAVING cnt > 30 LIMIT 5 OFFSET 0; SHOW META LIKE 'total_found';" | grep total_found | grep -oE '[0-9]+'); echo "Page 1 total_found: $TOTAL_FOUND_PAGE1"
––– output –––
Page 1 total_found: 199
––– comment –––
TEST 4: Pagination page 2 (OFFSET 5) - check total_found
––– input –––
TOTAL_FOUND_PAGE2=$(mysql -h0 -P9306 -e "SELECT category, COUNT(*) as cnt FROM test_having GROUP BY category HAVING cnt > 30 LIMIT 5 OFFSET 5; SHOW META LIKE 'total_found';" | grep total_found | grep -oE '[0-9]+'); echo "Page 2 total_found: $TOTAL_FOUND_PAGE2"
––– output –––
Page 2 total_found: 199
––– comment –––
CRITICAL: Verify total_found stable across pages (main issue #3428 complaint)
––– input –––
if [ "$TOTAL_FOUND_PAGE1" = "$TOTAL_FOUND_PAGE2" ]; then echo "SUCCESS: total_found stable for pagination (both pages show: $TOTAL_FOUND_PAGE1 total groups)"; else echo "FAIL: PAGINATION BROKEN - total_found differs across pages (Page1: $TOTAL_FOUND_PAGE1, Page2: $TOTAL_FOUND_PAGE2)"; fi
––– output –––
SUCCESS: total_found stable for pagination (both pages show: 199 total groups)
––– comment –––
TEST 5: Verify total_found counts groups (~200), not rows (10000)
––– input –––
if [ "$TOTAL_WITH_HAVING" -lt 10000 ] && [ "$TOTAL_WITH_HAVING" -gt 0 ]; then echo "SUCCESS: total_found ($TOTAL_WITH_HAVING) counts groups, not rows (10000)"; else echo "FAIL: total_found should count groups, not individual rows"; fi
––– output –––
SUCCESS: total_found (199) counts groups, not rows (10000)
––– comment –––
TEST 6: Edge case - HAVING filters everything (should return 0)
Old bug: would return 200 (all groups), new: should return 0
––– input –––
TOTAL_EMPTY=$(mysql -h0 -P9306 -e "SELECT category, COUNT(*) as cnt FROM test_having GROUP BY category HAVING cnt > 10000; SHOW META LIKE 'total_found';" | grep total_found | grep -oE '[0-9]+'); echo "Impossible filter (cnt > 10000) result: $TOTAL_EMPTY groups"
––– output –––
Impossible filter (cnt > 10000) result: 0 groups
––– comment –––
TEST 7: Verify stricter HAVING produces fewer results (cnt>60 ≤ cnt>30)
––– input –––
TOTAL_HAVING_GT_60=$(mysql -h0 -P9306 -e "SELECT category, COUNT(*) as cnt FROM test_having GROUP BY category HAVING cnt > 60 LIMIT 1; SHOW META LIKE 'total_found';" | grep total_found | grep -oE '[0-9]+'); echo "Groups with cnt > 60: $TOTAL_HAVING_GT_60"
––– output –––
Groups with cnt > 60: 15
––– input –––
if [ "$TOTAL_HAVING_GT_60" -le "$TOTAL_WITH_HAVING" ]; then echo "SUCCESS: More restrictive filter produces fewer results (cnt>60: $TOTAL_HAVING_GT_60 ≤ cnt>30: $TOTAL_WITH_HAVING)"; else echo "FAIL: Logic error - stricter condition should not increase group count"; fi
––– output –––
SUCCESS: More restrictive filter produces fewer results (cnt>60: 15 ≤ cnt>30: 199)
